'''Ōhirasan Shrine''' (おおひらさんじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in {{ill|lt=Tochigi|Q44830|WD=Q44830|1=Tochigi (city)}}, {{ill|lt=Tochigi Prefecture|Q44843|WD=Q44843|1=Tochigi Prefecture}}. Under the {{ill|lt=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|Q712534|WD=Q712534|lt=former ranking system|1=Modern system of ranked Shinto shrines}}, it was a prefectural shrine.

=== Overview ===
The shrine stands at the summit of {{ill|lt=Mount Ōhira (Tochigi)|Q11443944|WD=Q11443944|lt=Mount Ōhira|1=Mount Ōhira}}, and the stone staircase on the front approach has about 1,000 steps. It is said to have been founded in 827 by Jikaku Daishi ({{ill|lt=Ennin|Q732282|WD=Q732282|1=Ennin}})<ref>[http://www.kuranomachi.jp/spot/ohirasan/jinja/ Tochigi City Tourism Association]</ref>.

=== Main enshrined deities ===
It enshrines {{ill|lt=Ninigi|Q1056017|WD=Q1056017|lt=Ninigi-no-Mikoto|1=Ninigi-no-Mikoto}}, {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|WD=Q455602|lt=Amaterasu-Ōmikami|1=Amaterasu}}, and {{ill|lt=Toyouke-hime|Q2983724|WD=Q2983724|lt=Toyouke Ōkami|1=Toyouke-hime}}.

=== Cultural properties ===
;Tangible cultural properties designated by the city
*Zuishin Gate (designated December 21, 1961)
**Ceiling painting "Dragon" (designated December 21, 1961)
*Main sanctuary (designated December 18, 2008)
*Worship hall (designated December 18, 2008)
*Hoshimiya Shrine building (designated December 18, 2008)

=== Other ===
The stone staircase on the approach is called Ajisai-zaka (Hydrangea Slope). Around 2,500 hydrangea plants of various kinds are planted there<ref>Yomiuri Shimbun, Tochigi edition, June 20, 2016, p.31.</ref>.

=== Access ===
*From {{ill|lt=Tochigi Station|Q7811990|WD=Q7811990|1=Tochigi Station}}, about 15 minutes by {{ill|lt=Kantō Jidōsha (Tochigi)|Q11655986|WD=Q11655986|lt=Kantō Bus|1=Kanto Transportation}} on the Kokugakuin Line; get off at "Kokugakuin."
*About 15 minutes from {{ill|lt=Tochigi Interchange|Q11110314|WD=Q11110314|lt=Tochigi IC|1=Tochigi interchange}}

